          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and study and is a treatise from the Vedānta school of philosophy and is the fourth section of a larger work. It is a foundational work for this branch of Hindu philosophy from the early medieval period and was highly influential on later medieval thinkers and beyond. Particular concern is given to the nature of the highest reality or absolute, the brahman.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Brahmasūtra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">ब्रह्मसूत्र</title>
